##A call from Wuhan Square Cabin: I am going to save my grandmother | story FM

Story

Features, welcome to the story FM. Here, we tell your story with your voice. Every Monday, Wednesday and Friday, all platforms are updated simultaneously.

We strongly suggest that you listen to the Audio Program!

Click on the picture above to jump to the "story FM" applet and listen to the real person. Remember to add "my little program" , one-click to listen to the whole story Yo!

It has been nearly a month since the city was sealed off in Wuhan.

During this time, we got in touch with many listeners in Wuhan, hoping to find out if they were healthy and well.

On February 12, one of our listeners, Alain, told us that all four members of his family had suspected symptoms of new crown pneumonia. We contacted her immediately, hoping to document the family's fate.

It turns out, things are moving much faster than we thought.

During this time, every day at 20:30, we would talk to her on the phone, and this voice call also became her tree hole, collecting what she had seen and heard all day and nowhere to vent her feelings.

We put three days of the call into this program, also invited you to pick up, listen to the story of read.

First Call: A death card

Hello, my name is Daniel. I'm 26 years old.

On January 19, I took the high-speed train back to Wuhan for the Spring Festival. I began to suffer from diarrhea and high fever a few days later.

I haven't been outside since I got back from Beijing. I don't think it's pneumonia.

My friends warned me to be careful, so I went online, and the result was the common cold plus enterocolitis.

Then on February 6th, my grandmother started vomiting and couldn't eat. My mother said to send the old man to the hospital, but at that time the situation in Wuhan has been very severe, I am afraid that there was no disease, sent to infected how to do.

So I've been insisting that the old man stay at home. And now it seems to have delayed my old man a little.

■ anen does grandma's on-line consultations

And then my grandmother became completely unable to eat, and it was really dangerous, and my mom said, you have to try anyway. "

On the night of February 10th, my parents took my grandmother to the hospital and left me alone.

That night was really hard, 3 o'clock in the morning, my father called me: "you quickly pack up to do a test, your mother and your grandmother may be suspicious. ". "

Hearing this sentence of the moment, I really feel in front of a dark, as if something fell down, heavily on my body.

After the C.T. at the hospital, I went to see my grandmother.

She was lying on a chair with three bottles of water in her hands, a little half unconscious and very weak.

And I heard her say, "it's cold, it's cold. 'I took off my down jacket and threw it over her.

In a flash, grandma reacted very strongly, she said, "you put it on, it's cold! "! "The words hit my heart and made me sick.

I was so scared it was the last thing she said to me.

The CT results showed that, except for me, all of my family members had bilateral lung infections, and the blood routine had inflammation, which was suspected to be viral pneumonia. I had a single lung with a fibroid lesion and no inflammation, which was very mild.

A few hours later, we were able to schedule the nucleic acid test again.

You go into a dark room, like a hospital syringe, with two little round holes in it, and you stick your head in there. The doctor inside would poke a long cotton swab up her nose, and she would turn and scratch the cartilage in her nasal cavity, which was painful.

NUCLEIC ACID test

There is a sense of cool air from the nasal cavity through the sky cover, I grew up so big for the first time know that I had such a long way in the nasal cavity, the feeling of winding path.

NUCLEIC ACID results should be online in about two or three days. At noon on February 13th, my dad checked his own, and when he found it was negative, he was so happy, like he'd won an Olympic medal, and he posed as a winner.

I thought my dad was all negative, so I'm sure I'm okay, so I just ran a couple of cards, and I sent a screenshot to our family group, and I was like, "look, I'm negative. "

After a while, my father looked at me very seriously and said, "son, no, how can you be positive? "! "

It was the first time I'd ever seen my dad so broken, his hands on the table, and he kept saying, "it's not you. It's wrong. The four of us are connected. We're positive. "

One Minute he's excited that his test came back negative, and now he's saying it's not me, it's one of the three of them.

It's like, I drew a death card, and they said, "No, you didn't draw this card. "

Everyone wishes they'd picked the death card themselves.

Call number two: Patient 64

I came to the "Wuhan Living Room" Shelter Hospital the same day I found out the nucleic acid result.

Although my grandmother test results are negative, but according to the clinical diagnosis, determined to be serious pneumonia, was sent to the Vulcan Mountain Hospital treatment.

My parents are isolated in different places, and my family is scattered all over the place.

Almost everyone in the shelter has their own difficulties. People are so close to each other that they really share the same pain.

Patient a: Don't cry. What's going on in your room? Five in my room, four in hers.

Patient B: There's a seven-year-old kid at home alone with no one to take care of him.

Read: Don't cry, this is the community must manage, you call the community complaints, or call the mayor hotline, or I help you call.

Patient C: You need to get help on the Internet.

A: You have to be strong, at this time women is a very strong spiritual support, men are not as strong as women, he will soon collapse, the more women at this time, the more resilient. My family is my wife now, running the show. I used to do a lot of big things, but now she's the heart and soul of this family, and so are you. You can't fall apart. You have to be strong.

My family is my wife now, running the show. I used to do a lot of big things, but now she's the heart and soul of this family, and so are you. You can't fall apart. You have to be strong.

■ The "Wuhan Living Room" shelter hospital where Anin lives

This morning, the big sister in bed 64 next door seemed to be getting worse, and the doctor said she needed to be transferred.

As she sat on the edge of the bed, I looked at her with mixed feelings, as if I had seen my future destiny.

She had Caroline Zhang's face and eyes, chestnut curls, and a delicate face that did not hide the years.

All of a sudden, she gave me a big smile and said, "they said I had to be transferred. That can't be good, can it? I think it's getting worse? "

■ Nien and sister 64 have crossed paths several times over breakfast

I don't know how to answer that. And then she told me her story.

The husband of elder sister got cerebral artery Hemangioma, had an operation recently, because elder sister has been in the hospital to take care of him all the time, contracted pneumonia virus.

She also has a 16 year old son, whose husband is now unattended, and the three of them are stuck in different places, unable to bond.

I am very worried that my sister has not yet told his mother the truth, every day to pretend that everything is all right and her mother reported safe.

"If I tell the old man, will she live? "

And I didn't ask any more, and she said to herself, "don't tell her yet. What if I live? "

If you've ever seen someone look desperate, you won't forget it.

After tidying up, my sister lay in bed, her eyes fixed on the ceiling, not knowing what to think.

After a while, she covered her face with her army coat and cried in secret for a while.

I was there to witness her mood, and there was nothing I could do.

I felt very tired today, and then I fell asleep. When I woke up, there was an empty bed.

The empty bed 64

Everything that was taped to her bedside, about her name, her doctor, her condition, it all disappeared.

I used to be afraid that someone I knew would be a number in the statistics, and I ended up being a diagnosis myself, a number on some list.

The sister may be another number, but I'll never know.

All I know is that she's number 64.

Call number three: growing up overnight

Today I finally saw the square dance!

At noon, music began to play on the loudspeakers in the middle of the shelter, and we all gathered around. At the beginning of the breathing exercises jump, very simple action, do not do a few times I was tired.

Later, when they really dance in the square, I saw tears fall down, really burning.

Especially today in the dance group of C Lady, Wearing Pink Coral Velvet Pajamas, very confident to teach everyone how to dance.

■ Ah Nien is dancing in the square

Then someone asked her, can you dance to this song? She shook her head confidently. "I never pick music. I can dance to any kind of music. "

I was moved. Through the mask, I could see her smile, and though the whole experience might have been painful, at the moment, she was happy.

To tell you the truth, all I hear here every day is crying, which is really sad.

Then I got a phone call from my mom, and she said, "ask if you can transfer to Vulcan Mountain, your grandmother is not very eager to survive right now, she is in pain, do not want to live. ". My mom wants me to come over and take care of her.

Nini's grandmother

After I applied for a nurse, my dad came to see me.

They knew what was going on with grandma, but they never told me, and they thought if I knew, I'd go.

But Vulcan Mountain was more dangerous than the shelter, and my dad said, "you can't trade your 20-year-old life for your grandmother's 90-year-old life. "

To tell the truth, I used to think it wasn't worth it for a young man to save an old man, especially if the young man was a top student.

But there is no measure in the family, no worth it.

My mother was in so much pain, her mother on one side, her daughter on the other, and she tried to save them, but she couldn't hold them.

■ Ah Nien and her parents

She said, "maybe she won't make it. At least you'll get to see her one last time. And let her go in peace. "

Hearing my mother say such words, my heart is like a knife, I want to go to Vulcan Mountain now.

But the transfer of the matter is not so simple, not only need the shelter here to let people, Vulcan Mountain beds free, but also the approval of the relevant departments.

I packed my things, sat on the bed, and waited for them to ask me to transfer, but it never came.

My parents came up to me, and they videotaped me, and they said, "you're too young, your symptoms are too mild, and you're not allowed to go. "

I was subconsciously suspicious, and I was angry, "are you lying to me, not wanting me to go? "

My father said darkly, "don't you think, Vulcan mountain bed so scarce, that one empty bed has other serious patients need, can not let two beds only save your grandmother. ". "

I think he's right.

So far, I think a lot of things are right, but why is it so unpleasant?

We have so many tradeoffs between selfishness and selflessness, and I know exactly what needs to be done, but I still have selfish thoughts.

All I could think about at the time was, would the image of me covering up my grandmother be the last time we saw each other?

Today, while applying for a transfer, I was crying on the ground. A woman next to me asked what was wrong. I told her the situation briefly.

She said, "what's the big deal? My mom died yesterday. We all did. "

I certainly don't accept that pain can not be measured and compared.

But you can feel, here, all the emotions are like waves, high and low. A wave hit over, people inconsolable, the next moment, perhaps she stood in the square dance line, struggling to dance.

You can't see their grief.

I can't wait to get to Vulcan Mountain right now, but I don't want to bother the doctors and the nurses, and I don't want to break my dad, and every choice is hard.

In my parents'eyes, I was still a child held in the palm of my hand, especially childish.

But I grew up in a very painful way, it is not gradual, is the era of the hand pull out of the ground, I pulled out of the ground, pulling all my emotions.

It's like everything is different now. People like my dad, who talks like a bitch, have been giving us red envelopes every day:

I love you all, and I look forward to your return.

——————

On February 19, read was allowed to transfer to the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, now day and night non-stop to take care of grandma.

On the day of the transfer, she wrote four words on Weibo: no turning back.

Ah Nien, I hope you can come back safely and healthily. We will wait for you in Beijing.
